                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="483.0" layoutY="402.0" prefHeight="99.0" prefWidth="546.0" text="4. In a small bowl, whisk together 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 2 tablespoons of rice vinegar, 2 tablespoons of hoisin sauce, 1 tablespoon of sugar, 1/2 cup of vegetable broth (or water), and 1 tablespoon of cornstarch. Set the sauce aside." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="483.0" layoutY="505.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="486.0" text="5. In the same skillet, add 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil. Add minced garlic, ginger, and dried red chili peppers. Stir-fry for about 30 seconds until fragrant." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
